# Tagging & Compliance Standards

## Mandatory Tags
All resources must include these tags:
- **Service**: Name of the service/application
- **Environment**: dev, staging, prod
- **Owner**: Team or individual responsible
- **ManagedBy**: Always "Shinobi"
- **CostCenter**: Business unit for cost allocation

## Compliance Tags
- **compliance:framework**: "fedramp-low" | "fedramp-moderate" | "fedramp-high"
- **compliance:ssp-id**: System Security Plan identifier
- **compliance:data-classification**: "public" | "internal" | "confidential" | "restricted"
- **compliance:retention**: Data retention period in days
- **compliance:encryption**: "required" | "optional" | "none"

## Data Classification Requirements
- **Storage Resources**: S3, RDS, DynamoDB must have data-classification
- **Public Data**: No encryption required, can be publicly accessible
- **Internal Data**: Encryption at rest required, VPC-only access
- **Confidential Data**: Encryption at rest and in transit, audit logging
- **Restricted Data**: FIPS 140-2 encryption, dedicated infrastructure

## Framework-Specific Requirements

### Commercial (fedramp-low)
- Basic encryption (AES-256)
- Standard monitoring and logging
- Basic access controls
- Standard backup retention (7 days)

### FedRAMP Moderate
- Enhanced encryption (AWS KMS with customer-managed keys)
- Comprehensive monitoring and alerting
- Multi-factor authentication
- Extended backup retention (30 days)
- Network segmentation

### FedRAMP High
- FIPS 140-2 Level 3 encryption
- Continuous monitoring and SIEM integration
- Hardware security modules (HSM)
- Extended backup retention (90 days)
- Dedicated infrastructure with air-gapped networks

## Tag Enforcement
- **Deployment-time validation**: Tags validated before resource creation
- **Policy enforcement**: OPA/Rego policies check tag compliance
- **Cost allocation**: Tags used for detailed cost reporting
- **Compliance reporting**: Automated compliance dashboards

## Tag Management
- **Centralized tagging**: Tags defined in service.yml manifest
- **Environment inheritance**: Base tags with environment-specific overrides
- **Tag policies**: SCPs prevent untagged resource creation
- **Tag remediation**: Automated tagging of existing resources